    <prp:abstract>We aim to image the AGN jet-driven molecular outflow and a candidate nuclear HCN maser disk in nucleus of the Seyfert 2 galaxy M51 with the HCN(1-0) line at a ~0.1" (~3 pc) resolution. Our past observations toward this source with IRAM PdBI and SMA at a linear resolution of 10-30 pc in the CO and HCN lines show AGN jet-driven outflow with strong enhancement of HCN along the AGN jets. In addition, we also detected strong HCN emission only at the systemic velocity, similar to the systemic velocity component of the water maser emission from AGNs, suggesting the existence of an HCN maser disk surrounding the nucleus. In this proposal, we will (1) image the outflow with the HCN(1-0) and SiO(2-1) lines to distinguish the mechanism of how the narrow jets entrain the molecular gas outward, and (2) try to detect the high velocity component of the HCN maser that often seen in the water maser disks in AGNs. If we succeeded to detect the high velocity component, we will check the velocity shift using the high positional accuracy of the interferometer, and measure the black hole mass. If this succeeds, we will have another new tool to estimate the black hole mass in galaxies very accurately.</prp:abstract>
